A VIGILANT cop made an arrest of three South African Social Security Agency (Sassa) fraud suspects at Mangrove Beach Centre in Durban, KZN. She spotted three suspicious-looking women withdrawing money at an ATM on Tuesday, 3 January.  KZN cops spokesman Colonel Robert
Netshiunda said the young officer requested back-up from the Metro Police officers who were in the vicinity and strategically approached the suspects. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments  "The three suspects, aged between 24 and 39, were reportedly found in possession of over R60 000 in cash, 32 Sassa cards, 22 bank cards from various banking institutions, as well as four cellphones," Netshiunda said.